Nested Class Summary
 class EPlusEquipment.DaylightingControls
          class that defines the daylighting control of a specific zone
Assumptions:
There is only one reference point This reference point is located .8 m above the center of the floor Face Default illumination level requested is 500 lux Dimming is continuous and can go down to null power and null luminance (no manipulation probability) Glare index is not meaningful Careful with non convex zones since the reference point may end up outside the zone.
 class EPlusEquipment.ElectricEquipment
          class that defines the electric equipment of a specific zone
Assumptions:
No latent heat production (no moisture) No heat lost by producing work or ventilated outside the building assumes by default a predefined schedule These assumptions correspond to electronic equipment
By default the equipment power is defined in Watts and the general value 150 W is used.
 class EPlusEquipment.IdealLoadAirSystem
          class that defines HVAC ideal load air system for a specific zone
Assumptions:

TODO allow more definition of parameters
 class EPlusEquipment.Lights
          class that defines the lighting of a specific zone
Assumptions:
Suspended fluorescent Lighting is assumed (TODO switch to LED) No heat in the return air coming from the lights assumes by default a predefined schedule By default the lighting level is defined in Watts/Area and the general value of 10 W/m2 is used.
 class EPlusEquipment.People
          class that defines the amount of people occupying a specific zone
Assumptions:
No comfort model will be computed The fraction of radiant heat is 0.3 These assumptions correspond to electronic equipment
By default the people presence is defined in Area/Person and the general value 20m2 is used.
 class EPlusEquipment.Thermostat
          defines a thermostat which follows the heating and cooling sset point schedules provided
